name: water-environment-research-foundations-national-center-for-resource-recovery-and-nutrient-
notes: The goal of the Center is to provide innovative data, demonstrations, and tools to catalyze a paradigm shift in the water quality community; one where nutrients (N&amp;P) are not regarded as wastes, but rather valuable resources and an integral part of a sustainable managed system that includes the nutrients, energy, and water. WERF will administer the Center. All research activities will be led by university researchers and conducted by teams of subject matter experts at universities, wastewater utilities, non-profit community organizations and commercial animal facilities. This proposal contains four named academic subawards and three requests for proposals to be administered through WERF&#39;s competitive process. The Center&#39;s communication and outreach to the broad water quality stakeholder community will be supported by several well-respected national organizations and institutions.
title: Water Environment Research Foundation's National Center for Resource Recovery and Nutrient Management
